article.headline: Wright St. 60, South Florida 43
article.story: GUAYNABO, Puerto Rico -- Todd Brown scored 15 points and Wright State defeated South Florida on Sunday. South Florida shot 27.1 percent from the field (13 of 48), including a 0-for-12 performance from Dominique Jones. Wright State (5-7) scored nine unanswered points to brake away from a 9-9 tie with 13:46 left in the first half. The Raiders led 18-9 with 4:05 left in the first half on a John David Gardner jump shot. The Bulls (4-6) were 4-for-21 in the first half, and trailed 21-14 at halftime of the San Juan Shootout. The Raiders opened the second half with eight unanswered points, taking a 29-14 lead on a Todd Brown jump shot with 12:46 Left to play. Jesus Verdejo scored 26 points for the Bulls, who shot 44.4 percent from the free-throw line (12 of 27). Gardner added 11 for Wright State and N'Gai Evans scored 11.
